metadata.value: Bibliothèque nationale de France, Département des Manuscrits

description:
Copied by several scribes; [one of these][1] also wrote most of [ChiL s.s.][2] and last three pieces in [LucAS 184][3], [another][4] also wrote ff. b'-c of [ChiL s.s.][2] (PirrPT). [Scribe of ff. 99'-111][5] also wrote fragments now preserved in [Florence, Biblioteca Nazionale Centrale, Incunab. F.5.5][6] (FabbriSC). Probably copied in Florence (ReaneyP); fascicles 6 and 8 copied in Lucca (GüntA). Originally owned by Gino Capponi of Florence (GüntDM); Paolo da Firenze perhaps associated with compilation, but not as scribe (PirrPT). Owned in 19th century by Charles X, King of France (1756-1836); manuscript may have reached Paris via French branch of Capponi family. Later passed to Bibliothèque Nationale.


  [1]: https://www.diamm.ac.uk/people/4254/
  [2]: https://www.diamm.ac.uk/sources/667/
  [3]: https://www.diamm.ac.uk/sources/142/
  [4]: https://www.diamm.ac.uk/people/4255/
  [5]: https://www.diamm.ac.uk/people/4253/
  [6]: https://www.diamm.ac.uk/sources/675/#/
